This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it focuses on using natural language as a parameter space to improve the generality and efficiency of learned classifiers and control policies. Additionally, the paper mentions pretraining a language interpretation model to transform inputs into outputs given natural language descriptions, which is a common technique in natural language processing. 

The paper also involves machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of natural language as a parameter space could be seen as a form of representation learning, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

The paper's focus on learning classifiers and control policies suggests that it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper's use of images and reinforcement learning suggests that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.RO (Robotics), respectively.
